The paper proposes a machine learning method for identifying schizophrenia based on functional connectivity features. The method is a multi-kernel capsule network, which is a type of deep neural network. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as the method involves analyzing brain connectivity data.
